# Patch 0023 — Kavacha theme engine: load & apply theme packages live
# (ROADMAP Phase 3 "Theme engine loads theme packages"; ADR 0008).
#
# WHAT: KavachaThemeEngine.sys.mjs loads theme packages (manifest.json +
# colors.json + optional style.css; see theme-manifest.schema.json) and
# applies the active one (pref kavacha.theme.active) to browser chrome,
# swappable at runtime. Built-in packages (kavacha-midnight, and a second
# deep-evergreen dark theme kavacha-forest) are embedded token maps; USER /
# marketplace themes load from the profile kavacha-themes/<id>/ directory
# through the same apply path.
#
# RELATIONSHIP TO 0016: 0016 bakes Midnight into zen-theme.css and sets
# `--zen-branding-dark: var(--kavacha-surface)`, from which Zen's whole
# color-mix chain derives. The engine REUSES that bridge — to switch themes it
# overrides only the base --kavacha-* tokens (inline, !important, on the chrome
# root) and Zen re-tints. Default (kavacha-midnight) = clear overrides and let
# the baked floor show (zero flash); any other theme = inline token override +
# optional style.css as a per-window windowUtils AUTHOR_SHEET (the chrome-only
# mechanism from patch 0012; never touches web content).
#
# WHY NOT A PREF/OVERLAY: runtime package loading, live swap, per-window sheet
# lifecycle, and profile-directory discovery are logic, not a static default.
# ACCENT POLICY: themes tint surfaces only; the engine never writes
# --zen-primary-color / zen.theme.accent-color (owned by the welcome flow,
# patch 0017). KNOWN LIMIT: base-token override fills only the dark half of
# light-dark(), so both bundled themes are dark; light themes are a follow-up.
#
# NOT BUILD-VERIFIED: authored without a local Zen checkout; modified-file
# hunks are reconstructed against the post-0022 tree (they include 0022's
# lines because 0023 applies after it). Run `git apply --check` + Marionette
# before marking verified. Touches: zen-command-palette.ftl, moz.build,
# ZenStartup.mjs, KavachaCommandRegistry.sys.mjs; adds
# KavachaThemeEngine.sys.mjs. Applies on top of 0022.
